Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} ready for your pasta. Peel and
finely dice the @garlic clove{2} and the @onion{1}(peeled and finely diced).
Finely chop the @dill{4}. Grate the zest of the @lemon{1} and squeeze the juice
into a small #bowl{}. Cut the ends off your @purple sprouting broccoli{300%g} and
cut in half lengthways.

Put the @wheat tagliatelle{440%g} in the boiling water for ~{11%minutes} or until
just 'al dente'. Add the broccoli for the last ~{4%minutes} of cooking. Drain
but keep some of the pasta water.

As soon as you put the pasta in, put a large pan over a medium heat with
@butter{1%tbsp} or @vegetable oil{1%tbsp}. Add the onion and cook for
~{4%minutes}. Add the garlic and 2 tsp of lemon zest and cook for a further
~{1%minute}.

Flake the @hot smoked salmon{1.5%fillets} into the pan. Add @crème fraîche{6%tbsp},
4 tbsp of pasta water, 2 tsp of lemon juice and 2 tbsp of dill.

Add the drained pasta and broccoli and give everything a really good toss with
@salt{1/2%tsp} and @pepper{a good few grinds}. Tip: If the pasta looks dry add
some more pasta water.

Divide your pasta between your bowls and sprinkle over the remaining dill and
let your taste buds take a trip to La Isla Bonita.